    "impactStatement": "eLife reviews research in which approaches from the physical sciences are used to provide insights into the properties of biological systems and processes. Learn more about <a href=\"https://elifesciences.org/about/aims-scope#physics-living-systems\">what we review</a> and <a href=\"https://elifesciences.org/content-alerts?utm_source=website&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=physics-living-systems\">sign up for the latest research</a>.",
    "aimsAndScope": [
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "We aim to review studies in which experimental, theoretical, and computational approaches, rooted in the physical sciences, are developed and/or applied to provide deep insights into the collective properties and function of multicomponent biological systems and processes. We also welcome descriptions of methods that could enable the interrogation of classes of biological systems in new ways, as well as interdisciplinary studies that bring together scientists and approaches from the physical and life sciences. Read the <a href=\"https://elifesciences.org/subjects/physics-living-systems\">latest research</a> in this subject area."
        }
    ]
